  m_Name: Mushroom_18_Moonring
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Hollowfen.Data.MushroomFieldGuideData
  _id: moonring
  _commonName: Moonring
  _latinName: Unrecorded
  _edibility: 4
  _edibilityLabel: "Unknown \u2014 old knowledge"
  _description: 'A ring-forming mushroom from Sable''s seedbook, drawn as a broken circle of pale caps in a Deep Wood clearing. The old hand claims the rings widen under a full moon; the newer hand does not argue.'
  _idFeatures:
  - Pale caps growing in wide rings or arcs
  - Found in Deep Wood clearings, never open pasture
  - Ring persists year to year, widening
  _habitat: Deep Wood clearings
  _season: Unknown — the seedbook says autumn moons
  _lookalikes: Fairy-ring species of open grass — but nothing honest grows in rings this deep in the wood.
  _notes: 'Known only from Sable''s seedbook. Collection is a matter for someone who understands what the rings are for.'
